com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetSystemTrustSettingsRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetSystemTrustSettingsRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SystemProvider, Serializable

    public class GetSystemTrustSettingsRequest
extends SiperianRequest
implements SystemProvider
    Retrieves the system-specific trust settings for the specified columns.

    A trust setting (see TrustSetting) is defined for a trust-enabled column for a particular system (see setSystemName(String)). If a system is not specified, the trust settings for the Admin system will be returned.

    Required Parameter:

    • setColumnUids(ArrayList) - Specifies the list of columns for which the trust settings will be retrieved.

    Usage Example:

    The following example retrieves the trust settings for the column FIRST_NAME in base object C_CONTACT:

    GetSystemTrustSettingsRequest request = new GetSystemTrustSettingsRequest();
    ArrayList columnUids = new ArrayList();
    columnUids.add("C_CONTACT|FIRST_NAME");
    request.setColumnUids(columnUids); //Required
    request.setSystemName("WEB"));
    GetSystemTrustSettingsResponse response =
    (GetSystemTrustSettingsResponse) sipClient.process(request);

    See Also:
    SiperianObjectType, GetSystemTrustSettingsResponse, TrustSetting, SiperianClient.process(SiperianRequest), Serialized Form

    API Pair: GetSystemTrustSettingsResponse

    API Group: Data Steward
